the price of bread sugar and rice will 
increase by about 30 percent in the new year as part of the 
governments austerity plan to get international loans a newspaper 
reported 
the budapest daily nepszabadsag quoting managers at state food 
trading companies said flour cosmetics and other household goods 
also will increase 
these are suggested retail prices final prices will be 
determined by market conditions the paper said 
the increases are seen as necessary to revitalize industries 
whose traditional subsidies have been slashed by the government as 
it tries to qualify for credits from the international monetary 
fund 
the state railroads announced earlier in december that domestic 
fares would increase by 80 percent and the national telephone 
company is planning a 150 percent hike in phone charges 
postal services are going up by 40 percent and municipal bus 
fares by 55 percent early next year 
