<TEXT>
china is supplying new military 
aid to cambodias communist khmer rouge guerrillas despite its 
claim to have halted shipments months ago western intelligence and 
other sources say 
the sources also say the cambodian government is receiving 
support from thousands of vietnamese soldiers disguised as 
cambodians vietnam says it has withdrawn all its troops but the 
rebels have long disputed that 
the reports emerged this week as peace talks were stalled 
between the cambodian government and the resistance fighting has 
intensified in western cambodia over the past month 
the khmer rouge are loading trucks and trucks of new chinese 
ammunition said one western intelligence official who spoke on 
condition of anonymity there is a recent increase in chinese 
supplies to the khmer rouge 
other sources at the thai border town of aranyaprathet and 
elsewhere along the cambodian frontier said this week that the 
chinese are preparing fresh deliveries of ammunition in 
anticipation of a government offensive 
china is the main backer of the khmer rouge and two other 
guerrilla groups fighting the government vietnam installed after 
invading cambodia in late 1978 the khmer rouge which was ousted 
from power by the invasion is the strongest guerrilla army 
china said it had stopped military assistance after the five 
permanent members of the un security council including china and 
the united states adopted a peace plan for cambodia in late 
august 
since the five member countries of the security council 
adopted the five documents on cambodia china has not provided any 
military assistance including weapons to the cambodian 
resistance chinas foreign ministry spokesman li zhaoxing said 
last month 
the guerrillas have supported the un plan which calls for a 
truce followed by un involvement in the countrys administration 
and unsupervised elections but the vietnameseinstalled 
government has rejected key elements of the plan 
meanwhile government forces are preparing a major offensive in 
the approaching dry season western intelligence and guerrilla 
sources say 
they say the government is supported by vietnamese troops who 
have secretly returned to cambodia disguised as cambodian 
government soldiers 
vietnam says it withdrew all troops from cambodia in september 
1989 but western intelligence sources in bangkok say they believe 
there are 4000 to 9000 vietnamese military personnel in the 
country 
they say vietnam has supplied large amounts of ammunition to the 
government in recent months 
however one analyst predicted that if peace talks break up the 
khmer rouge is in a position to win the war 
if the phnom penh government chooses to fight it out with the 
khmer rouge they are making a big mistake said the intelligence 
analyst in bangkok 
khmer rouge support within the country is growing and they 
have the means to continue regardless of any international cutoff 
if this peace proposal fails it is out of the control of anyone 
but cambodians and in the long run it is the khmer rouge who will 
win 
during its rule from 197579 the khmer rouge killed hundreds of 
thousands of cambodians directly through purges and executions and 
indirectly through starvation and the hardship of a radical 
agrarian relocation program 
