headed a military dictatorship that ruled the former dutch colony 
from 198088 bouterse is widely believed to have planned the coup 
kraag belongs to the national party of suriname the party of 
ousted vice president henck arron wijdenbosch is chairman of the 
national democratic party which was organized by bouterse 
shankar and his cabinet formally submitted their resignations to 
the parliament friday the military claims surinames constitution 
permits military intervention as long as the national assembly is 
left intact 
shankars former coalition has 40 seats in the assembly and the 
national democratic party has three seats 
cmdr ivan graanoogst acting army chief said the new president 
will set the election date and the interim government will decide 
whether to allow international observers to monitor the elections 
bouterse met friday with lugo turon a special emissary from 
venezuelan president carlos andres perez and told him the army 
will keep its word and there will be elections an army statement 
said 
the ethnically diverse nation of 400000 people has suffered a 
progressive economic crisis since 1980 
