government pardons 
the onetime dictators former army gens jorge videla and 
roberto viola and montonero guerrilla founder mario eduardo 
firmenich walked free for the first time since 1984 
videla and viola were among 11 former officials mostly generals 
convicted of torture and other rights abuses who were pardoned 
under an order announced thursday by president carlos menem 
menem who last year freed 39 other generals and 64 terrorists 
said saturdays releases would definitely close a sad and black 
stage of argentine history 
the pardons however will reopen wounds for many argentines 
recent polls have shown up to 80 percent of the population opposed 
